description: As the FBI continues its assault on Abaddon's city of the damned, his actions have dire consequences for one of Jack Miller's students, while another inches closer to the truth.
Abaddon's crusade escalates. Agents Townsend and Benson make a discovery. David makes a deal.
The clues to Abaddon's origins begin to come together, revealing a strange connection to David's past. Meanwhile, Erin reveals a family secret, and David has doubts about his deal with the devil.

Lieutenant Deena Shan is feeling insecure and worthless. After a few nearly disastrous missions with the Rebel Alliance, she is ready to give up, go home, and leave the rebellion to the true heroes.

That is, until Deena becomes part of a "suicide" mission that could hit the Empire where it really hurts! But, when Luke Skywalker and Princess Leia are captured in process, Deena must reconcile herself to complete the mission and save these two figureheads of the Rebellion, and many others-single-handed!

Will she succeed, or will this be Deena's last mistake?
name: Volume 3

description:
Imperial officer Janek "Tank" Sunber makes a critical choice between his duty to the Empire and his loyalty to childhood friend Luke Skywalker in an explosive tale of Rebel spies, Imperial ambushes, and the dreaded Darth Vader!

Having rescued Rebel strategist Jorin Sol from the Empire, Luke Skywalker now leads X-Wing attack runs on Imperial convoys to rustle up much needed supplies for the Rebel fleet. Little does he know that within Sol lies a secret that will put the entire Alliance in danger. What's worse, when Luke receives a coded message from Lt. Sunber, he must decide whether to trust his old friend or obey the orders of Princess Leia who believes Tank may be part of an Imperial plot to capture the Rebellion's greatest hero!

A compelling new story set between the events of A New Hope and The Empire Strikes Back exploring the Rebel Alliance's struggle against the Galactic Empire.
name: Volume 1

volume.name: Star Wars: Rebellion - My Brother, My Enemy

description:
For years, Wyl Tarson, top lieutenant to the galactic crimelord Raze, secretly delivered valuable information to the Rebel Alliance-until his employer discovered the betrayal and implanted a bomb inside Wyl's skull!

Now, Wyl must infiltrate an Imperial stronghold on the planet Ahakista under the guise of working for the Rebellion, or Raze will detonate the bomb. Unwilling to compromise active Rebel agents, Wyl assembles a team of operatives too washed up or too crazy for the Alliance and leads them into a suicide mission that's his only chance for survival!

* Ancient tunnels, local militias, a conniving casino owner, and the dreaded Darth Vader all play a part in this riveting adventure set in the months after Star Wars: A New Hope!
name: Volume 2

volume.name: Star Wars: Rebellion - The Ahakista Gambit

description:
Anarchic 80s UK kids comic - first birthday issue.

Cover: Patrick Gallagher (Uncle Pigg)

  • Mary Lighthouse (Mark Rodgers - Ian Jackson)
  • Pete and his Pimple (Lew Stringer)
  • When Dinosaurs Ruled the Earth! (Marc Riley)
  • Hugo the Hungry Hippo (David Haldane)
  • Dead Fred - The Party from Beyond (Tony Husband - Wilkie)
  • The Pied Piper of Porksmouth (Dave Jones)
  • Psycho Gran (David Leach)
  • Greedy Gorb (Davy Francis)
  • Frank Sidebottom and Snatcher Sam in 'Don't Play it Again Sam!' (photo story)
  • Harry the Head (Marc Riley)
  • Burp (Banx)
  • Horace (Ugly Face) Watkins (Tony Husband)
  • Hector Vector and his Talking T-Shirt (Banx)
  • Oink Anniversary Portrait (centrespread poster of Oink! character) (Mark Rodgers - Ed McHenry)
  • Rubbish Man (David Haldane)
  • Tom Thug (Lew Stringer)
  • The Sekret Diary ov Hardian Vile - aged 8 5/8 (years) (Mark Rodgers - Ian Jackson)
  • Mister Big Nose (Banx)
  • Doctor Mooney - he's completely loony! (Marc Riley)
  • Invisible Charlie (Davy Francis)
  • Zoo Town (David Haldane)
  • Frank Sidebottom - Little Frank comes back from the Moon (Chris Sievey)
  • The History of Oink! comic (Graham Exton - Ian Jackson)
  • Billy's Brain - Brain Boggler! (Mark Rodgers - David Haldane)
  • Nothing Particularly out of the Ordinary Man (Davy Francis)
  • Anniversary of Horror (Tony Husband - Les 'Lezz' Barton)
  • Pete and his Pimple - Pete's Boily Badges (Lew Stringer)
  • Roger Rental - he's completely mental! (art: Ian Knox)
  • Spotty and Kreep (Sooty and Sweep parody) (creators: unknown)
name: Oink! 26 - Birthday issue

description:
Reprinting four classic Zenescope stories including Jack and the Beanstalk, Sinbad, Return to Wonderland and Neverland. This issue is perfect for introducing new fans to Zenescope and the Grimm Fairy Tales universe.

Also including in this edition is a new, never before published Grimm Fairy Tales story.
name: Grimm Fairy Tales #8; Sinbad #0; Return to Wonderland #0; Neverland #0; Unleashed: A Shadow Falls Bonus Prequel

description: The "Best comic of 2011" as voted by: Wizard World, Pop Culture Addict, Comic Buzz, Talking Comics, and Geekadelphia continues! A powered up Francis has kidnapped a helpless Mary. Now Eddie and the Hero must join forces to stop the unstoppable. Will they find a way to defeat the Francis or will they both fall to the power mad villain bent on getting his revenge against the man who destroyed his life? Set in a world where the super heroes aren't really heroes at all...how far would you go to FLY? From the writer of the Wonderland Trilogy, Irresistible, and The Waking, Fly is sure to stay on your pull list! Featuring over 29 pages of content for the mind blowing conclusion and final issue to the new FALL story arc!

"Endangered Species," The Conclusion! It's the most world-shattering story to ever hit Knuckles the Echidna, and it all ends here! As Team Fighters make their way to the Arctic, Thrash and Knuckles collide in an explosive final battle for the fate of the Echidnas. So why is Silver the Hedgehog in the mix? Find out in this exciting finale!
name: Endangered Species Finale: One Of A Kind

description: In the unrelenting battle with the Black Ghost, our double-O heroes have traveled around the world, dived to the murky depths of the oceans and rocketed to the cool, far reaches of outer space. All the while, the Black Ghost has paved a path for perpetual war...but now all roads must come to an end. In this grand finale, the Teflon team journeys deep into the ranks of the Black Ghost, all the way to its secret, central command! But what 009 finds will shock the mechanical daylights out of him. Will the Black Ghost pull the plug on the ennead ensemble once and for all? Or will the machines finally destroy their creator?
name: Vol. 10

description:
Experience the exclusive Emerald City Comicon '13 Atomic Robo digital comic everyone has been talking about. Created exclusively for comiXology, using comiXology's Guided View, and a digital comic that can only be experienced on comiXology - you've never read a comic like this before!

It's just another day in the life of Atomic Robo until a mysterious enemy from his past strikes! Wait, that really is just another day in the life of Atomic Robo. In fact, this time he doesn't even know who it is. Hey, when you've been around for 90 years, you lose track of all your nemeses.

volume.name: Atomic Robo: Two-Fisted Tales: Along Came A Tyrantula

description:
Marvel's cutting-edge Infinite Comics are back and this time it's the Guardians of the Galaxy that get the infinite digital treatment! Prepare to take to the spaceways with a reading experience like no other!

Drax is attacked by a Rigellian named Sacino in a space bar. He fights her and her team until they are defeated.

After the fight, Peter Quill finds him and asks him to join the Guardians of the Galaxy again. Drax reluctantly agrees.
name: Destroyed; Featuring: Drax

volume.name: Guardians of the Galaxy Infinite Comic

description: Get ready for the epic first collision of Bloodshot and Harbinger with this FREE look inside Valiant's first family crossover! Find out everything you need to know before Harbinger Wars #1 (of 4) hits stands this April right here with this free behind-the-scenes preview of the series that will define the Valiant Universe in 2013. Featuring exclusive artwork and character designs by Clayton Crain, Khari Evans and Clayton Henry!

EEEK! #7 delivers more weird tales of horror and suspense. This retro-style anthology of all-new horror tales is guaranteed to give you the eeries and the creepies! This issue features three all new horror tales; "The Harvest," "Deterrent Protocaol," and "The Green Fairy." PLUS--a horror pin up gallery by EEEK creator Jason Paulos. Taking a pinch of black humour from EC comics and mixing it with the art stylings of House of Mystery and Warren comics, EEEK! blends a heady broth that hits you like a burning incense stick to the retina. Jason Paulos delivers the goods with tales of revenge, zombies, vampires, ghouls and monsters. Each tale drawn in a different style reminiscent of the B&W horror mags of the 70's and 80's.

It's the motion picture event of the century as Hugh MacGlue's new action movie is about to premiere in GlobWorld. However, it seems that someone is planning to crash the premiere and spoil the event. Can the Globs stop a new bully from ruining their big day? Issue #2 is written by Jeremy Whitley (Princeless) with art from Chad Cicconi (Fracture) and features a backup illustrated by Andrew Charipar.

Lucy Goosey is trying to create the perfect recipe to make all of GlobWorld happy. However, when her cooking hits a snag she looks to the infallible Professor Floob for help. Can he fight the past and help Lucy make the perfect marshmallow bacon surprise? You'll have to read this issue to find out!

Hold on to your hats! Monty knows who is behind all the shenanigans that have been plaguing GlobWorld. Not even Monty is ready for the chaos that will break loose when he confronts the hidden bully. It will take all the mischief of all our favorite Globs to save GlobWorld. Will they be victorious?

With two more tales, Sharaz-de saves her people from the evil king for two more nights. She tells him of three brothers who inherit their father's fortune and care only for increasing their wealth, even at each other's expense, and the story of a happy man cursed by a dream of ill fortune.

name: The Fool Was I!; My Problem Sister; The Legend of Gretna Green; Hearts at Sea
How Cruel My Heart / They Met in Paris! / I Cheated at Love / Nobody To Trust / The Man I Lost

description: Flying whales, giant imaginary pink bunnies, friendly robots, curious aliens, space explorers, and adventures all find a home between the covers of this book. The Antler Boy and Other Stories collects ten short stories written and illustrated by Jake Parker, New York Times bestselling illustrator and creator of the Missile Mouse graphic novel series from Scholastic.
name: GN

volume.name: The Antler Boy and Other Stories

description: Humanity was on the brink of extinction when an alien race brought remarkable technology in the form of massive weapons of war. As mankind stepped into the galactic arena, they encountered the WASTERS, a threat unlike any seen before. In a final mission on a distant world, a squadron of mecha pilots get cut off from reinforcements and have to battle against all odds for survival as they discover dark secrets about their allies... secrets that could alter the balance of power in the universe!

A 6 issue series about slacker vampires sharing a house in Manchester. For Vince an eternity with nothing to do sounds ideal until he actually gets it and finds living forever requires something to live for. The first issue introduces Vince, a young University drop-out with no ambition, who has the worst and last day of his life, and things only go downhill from there.
name: 20th Century Vamp, Part 1

description: From the mind of Graeme Base, the award-winning creator of Animalia, The Eleventh Hour, and The Waterhouse, Arcana Comics is proud to present BREATHER. On the distant planet of Otarius, invaders from the Birshh Dynasty have captured and enslaved the native Otarans. Pushed on by the ruthless Governor, timid Dr. Bjrork conducts horrific experiments to create a superior breed of slave. Years later, Birshh-Otaran hybrids are raised in captivity, dependent on 'breathers' -- life-saving gasmasks that filter the Otarian air they, as hybrids, cannot tolerate. Two siblings, Dhrmmn and Lilli, strive to prove worthy of the Dynasty, to earn privileges for their half-breed kind.

A collection of european fairytales drawn by independent cartoonists such as KC Green, Lin Visel, Kel McDonald, Jose Pimenta, Kate Ashwin, Mary Cagle, Katie Shanahan, Shaggy Shanahan, and Kory Bing. Each picked a fairytale that was lesser known or one they could give a new spin on. Includes Bisclavret, The Singing Bone, the Pied Piper, Nixie of the Mill-Pond, Rapunzel, Puss and Boots, Tatterhood, and Jack and the Bean Stalk
name: Volume 1

description: Chloe Noonan is a monster hunter, but she doesn't have any powers. She can't beat up bad guys, she can't run without getting a stitch. She's kinda flakey and really not bothered about saving the world. Especially when she has to get the bus everywhere. Set in the fictional British town of Ravensdale, this ongoing series of comics and short stories sees our eponymous hero Chloe Noonan team up with a government led squad of Monster Hunters to solve the ever growing monster problem. This digital omnibus collects every Chloe Noonan story to date in full colour and comes complete with a cover illustration gallery, fan art section and a look into creator Marc (Ellerbisms, Love The Way You Love) Ellerby's sketchbook designs.
name: TPB

volume.name: Chloe Noonan: Monster Hunter: Digital Omnibus

description: The full archive of Diesel Sweeties begins here, with all comics from the year 2000. Marvel as girls date robots, hipsters exist before the word is even coined and sentient toasters make crumby friends.
name: Comics From the Year 2000

description: The cult autobiographical web-comic is finally released in a collection from Great Beast Comics. Ellerbisms is the story of a relationship told in pictures through the autobiographical comics of Marc Ellerby. Ellerbisms catches a glimpse into the life of a young couple, their highs and lows, their sighs and LOLs. Ellerbisms collects more than 200 original strips plus an additional 30 pages of brand new material exclusive to this edition.
name: TPB

description: Rebecca was hired to protect the self absorbed pop princess, Mistress Lala. Suddenly, freak accidents start happening every time Rebecca turns her back. It Takes all her skills and magical talents to juggle protecting Lala and figuring out what's behind these disasters.

Every week, millions take out their trash on Garbage Day, but thanks to a new memory tool called the Cartisan Device, people can erase a single day from their lives and consciousness as if it had never occurred. For down on his luck former Parole Officer Seth Mason, every day is one he would like to forget. He lost his job, his wife, and filed for bankruptcy. Everything changes when Seth is offered a job by "The Barker" to kill a local Detective Seth has some history with. Seth follows through, but guilt drives him to take out his Cartisan Device and throw away the day for good. When an error message shows up on the machine, Seth is on a race against time to forget the worst day of his life and untangle conflicts between memories and reality before it's too late!
name: GN

description: Collects Grounded #1-6. The good news: super-heroes are real. The bad news: You're not one of them. When Jonathan is sent to a high school for super-powered teens, he's forced to abadon his dream of having powers and deal with the reality that he's the only kid without them.
name: TPB

description: Fifteen year old Jason Stonewall and his father, Raymond Stonewall return to the American town of Brickhaven after a year long training sojourn overseas in the East. Now the young martial arts prodigy must deal with his first day as a freshman in high school, b-boy bullies, girls, Brickhaven High's most notorious gang, the SHO'GUNNZ and their menacing leader, the Banchō Gangsta - - FA'SHO!

Isis confronts a new threat, known as The Council, who plan to cleanse the world of all who reject their one true god. When Scott is taken hostage, Isis-- now completely powerless-- agrees to trade her freedom for his. After the trade is complete, The Council welcomes Isis into their holy sanctuary, where she comes face-to-face with their o'mighty god herself... and Isis quickly realizes the the only person who could stop this maddening cult is the god whose word they follow. This brand new collected edition features never before seen images and bonus material!
name: Volume 3

volume.name: The Legend of Isis: Dogs of War

description: Dr. Zareb Alter, a licensed telepathic therapist on Earth, has a problem. He is in reality Xenos DeFoncé, of the notorious DeFoncé crime organization of Hardcore Station and his family members are trying to pull him back into their dirty business. He is tasked with using his telepathic/telekinetic powers to find out who murdered Grimhold DeFoncé, the family's sinister patriarch. Once back on Hardcore Station, Xenos is forced to investigate his own family, a genetically altered collection of enhanced-powered psychopaths and other kinds of deviants. But the further Xenos' investigation progresses the more unanswered questions pop up. Something more is going on here and Xenos has to figure out what, if he hopes to survive this visit home.
name: GN

person_credits.name: Jim Starlin
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: On the eve of a great battle, a humble squire is tasked with delivering a letter to a seemingly abandoned castle at the heart of an ill-famed swamp. Met with mysterious apparitions on the way, he slowly unveils the truth behind his journey as his past is re-written over the course of the story.

Nathan Sorry did not die on 9/11. He ran. A missed flight saves Nathan Sorry from being in his office in the World Trade Center on the morning of 9/11 and leaves him with an inadvertently stolen laptop that contains the key to $20 million and a new identity. Two months later, Nathan is hiding out in a small town, calling himself “James Goode”, and is slowly losing his grasp of who he really is and what he's really running from.
name: Vol. 1

description: Dee's life is in turmoil when her parents are killed in a freak tornado. Returning to Kansas for the funeral after five years in LA, Dee discovers Emeraldsville is the same unexciting place it was when she left -- until the bizarre unexplained murders begin.
name: Volume One

volume.name: No Place Like Home: Home Again

description: These 14 (for February 14th, Valentine's Day!) Oscarina cartoons are about love and romance, from the lighthearted to the unwaveringly realistic, and always optimistic and philosophical. They're suitable for someone in love, someone single, someone young and inexperienced, as well as someone who's been around the block a few times. I like to think they're suitable for both sexes, but that depends on the individual, as do all things. :)
name: Volume 1

volume.name: Oscarina...: Eau de Pepper Spray (And Other Oscarina Cartoons About Love and Romance)

description: From horses to elephants, read about the pets that occupied the White House along with the many families that stayed there! A great book for all ages!

Meet Amy, a little girl with a big attitude! Enjoy as she inflicts all manner of suffering on her parents, without conscience or remorse! Her babysitter is Flower, who must also contend with the unwanted attentions of (lovesick) Dick. He's the friendly neighborhood stalker, totally besotted with Flower and never far way! Raising Amy -- she's armed, she's dangerous, and she's a proper Scottish ginger nutcase! Just be thankful she's not yours!
name: GN

description: The Magic returns like never before! Sabrina Spellman is your average teenager by day, attending Greendale High where her crush Harvey plays for the school basketball team. But by night, Sabrina enters the magic realm where she hones her witchcraft and attends charm school with the handsome and mysterious Shinji! Start from the very beginning as Sabrina deals with her two eccentric aunts and her conflicting lives in the Mortal and Magic realms, presented with a manga-style makeover! Amidst all the high school mischief, magic and romance, a real threat is growing in the Magic Realm -- and it may hit closer to home than Sabrina ever expected!
name: Volume 1

volume.name: Sabrina the Teenage Witch: The Magic Within

description: No single human being has been more inseparably tied to the twisted destinies of the terran, protoss, and zerg races than Sarah Kerrigan. She has risen from the ranks of soldier and rebel to become the unstoppable Queen of Blades, supreme ruler over a race of bloodthirsty aliens. But now she has fallen from her seat of power and been taken in by those who wish to separate the woman from the monster--a task which may be more difficult than it was to dethrone her. Take a look inside the mind of one of the greatest villains in gaming history and prepare yourself for StarCraft 2: Heart of the Swarm with this explosive new comic from Blizzard Entertainment, Kerrigan: Hope and Vengeance.

Donald Duck and Scrooge McDuck star in this classic thriller of splitting personalities. Strange things happen when Donald, as Doctor Duckell, experiments with some generosity formulas in search of a cure for stinginess. The result...Mister Duckyde!

volume.name: The Strange Case of Doctor Duckell and Mister Duckhyde

description: Something is amuck at Turkey Grove Farms. Jasper's dad, the famous face of the farm's commercials, hasn't been seen since before Thanksgiving. Why is Jasper telling anyone who will listen of a great turkey uprising? Has Jasper gone crazy or is this just another publicity stunt? One thing for is certain, business is booming and the turkey has never been more delicious. Everything evolves, why not turkeys?
name: OGN

description: Out in the Arctic Ocean, the research vessel Alesia manages to capture a mysterious Magnapinna squid, an animal never before captured by mankind. The researchers, led by Maria, decide to take the specimen back to port in Bergen, Norway. However, what they bring home isn't just a scientific wonder but also a thing more horrific than Pandora's Box. Soon, madness creeps into the crew of the Alesia and friends become monsters.
name: OGN

description: Chosen as one of IGN's Best Indie Series of 2011. Vic Boone is a blend of bizarre 50s Hollywood sci-fi and pulp detective noir set in a futuristic Portland, OR. Malfunction: Murder collects the first arc of the award winning series, including four previously unreleased Vic Boone shorts. Ex-motorcycle daredevil turned P.I., Vic Boone is hired by wealthy socialite Nina Hunt to clear her name of murder. Talking gorillas, mad scientists, and human flies--Vic Boone has it all.
name: Volume 1

description: Wyatt Earp, Geronimo, Belle Starr, Annie Oakley, and The Cisco Kid! This thrilling wide-vision graphic novel teams up these five legendary old-west characters for the first time anywhere, in a heart-pounding quest for justice deep in the dark heart of the New Mexico desert!

XIII and his friends have failed to recover Maximilian’s gold and are tired of hiding, running and struggling. When two books come out in the USA relating all the events of the amnesiac’s life and the details of the Conspiracy of the XX, they see it as a possible chance to come out in the open and trust in their country’s justice. But they still have enemies, at home and abroad, and everyone is set on a collision course...
name: The Last Round

description: The title says it all as Kolchak finds himself surrounded by creepy parts and pieces of science gone wrong! Is this what it seems like? Could it be reality, when it really started as fantasy from the past?

volume.name: Kolchak the Night Stalker and Dr. Moreau

description: When Nazi super-science launches a monster death-device against London, it's up to Captain Midnight and Commander X to stop the uber-destroyer! But even with back-up from Britannia, Valkyrie, Airboy, and the Air Fighters, can the heroes save the day against such overwhelming and unstoppable power?
name: The War to End All Wars

description:
Get ready to explore the Multiverse with theMatt Hatter Chronicles™ Magazine, based on the popular CITV programme and filled with incredible 3D content! Grab your copy from all good retailers now!

Here's what's inside:

All-new Matt Hatter Story!

It's time to put on your special Matt Hatter 3D Multivision Visor and enter the Multiverse! Join in the action in an all-new Matt Hatter comic strip adventure! A new Hatter Gadget has been discovered - an awesome Crossbow Blaster that will destroy any Spatter Trap. Can Matt get to it before Tenoroc's latest Super Villain, the deadly flying terror, Icarus?

Matt’s Gadget Guide

Get the lowdown on some of the amazing gadgets that help Matt and his gang in their battles with Tenoroc - including the Multivision Specs and Roxie's Staff!

Are you Matt enough?

Think you've got what it takes to be a Hatter Hero? Take this quiz, add up your Hatter points and find out whether you're like Matt, Gomez or Craw!

Design your own Multi-verse Monster!

Have you got a great idea for a new monster? Send in your ideas for a new monster for Tenoroc and you may even see it printed in the first issue of the Matt Hatter Chronicles Magazine in August! Click here to download an entry form!

How To Draw Matt Hatter

Follow the simple instructions to draw your very own Matt Hatter - then why not send in some of your drawings for us to include in the magazine! Send them to: Matt Hatter Magazine, 144 Southwark Street, London, SE1 0UP or email them to: matthatter@titanemail.com

Plus:

AWESOME pull-out poster!

Character guide

3D Multiverse Maze!

Win cool Spy Net gadgets!
name: Mad Hatter Chronicles

description:
The Joker is the most deadly foe Batman has ever faced – and the most personal, and unpredictable! But he’s been missing for a year, ever since he had his face sliced off in a bizarre and barbaric act! Now he’s back, and it looks like he’s trying to cut the Batman Family down to size! PLUS! It’s the senses-shattering return of BATMAN INCORPORATED. The next two Batman epics begin here! Don’t miss a minute of the greatest era of Batman ever!

Inside the latest issue:

BATMAN: DEATH OF THE FAMILY - KNOCK KNOCK

The Joker – last seen having his face cut off, over in The Dark Knight #1 – is back! But where has he been, and what has he been planning for a year?

First printed in Batman #13

BATMAN: DEATH OF THE FAMILY - FUNNY BONES

The Joker is re-enacting all his original crimes – but with deadly new twists. But what does Batman’s murderous court jester really want from him?

First printed in Batman #14

BATMAN INCORPORATED: LEVIATHAN - DEMON STAR

The definitive origin story of the all-new Robin, Damian Wayne! From birth to his first meeting with this father, this one’s got it all. Plus – get to know the ruthless Talia al Ghul: 2013 is going to be her year!

First printed in Batman Incorporated #1
name: The Joker Returns!

description:
Wow! We’ve got quite the roller coaster for you this issue, with two doses of BATMAN INCORPORATED! We cut to the quick of the international war against Batman, started by Talia al Ghul – aka Leviathan, and then follow it up with three short stories! Joker’s visiting his former partners in crime – Harley Quinn, Penguin and Riddler! What part will they play in Joker’s terrifying scheme to rid Batman of his partners, sidekicks and support network – permanently?

Inside this issue:

BATMAN INCORPORATED – Eye of the Gorgon

Leviathan stands revealed as Talia al Ghul… but what made Talia the woman she is today – with a burning hatred for the man she once called ‘beloved’… Bruce Wayne?

First printed in Batman Incorporated #2

BATMAN INCORPORATED – Brand Building

Before Leviathan tears it all apart in the present, go back, before The New 52, to find out how Batman built Batman Incorporated, how he recruited the Batmen of multiple nations to back up his plan – and how they became his international army of operatives!

First printed in Batman Incorporated #0

DEATH OF THE FAMILY – Tease, Men of Worship and Red Light, Green Light

Joker is back in Gotham – and he’s playing a visit to Batman’s rogue’s gallery. What part to Harley Quinn, Penguin and Riddler have to play in his terrifying plot against Batman?

First printed in Batman #13, #14 and #15

For the greatest adventures, the coolest competitions and the most super of heroes, look no further than Batman: The Brave and the Bold Comic!

Based on the hit TV animated series, learn more about the world’s greatest detective, with puzzles, quizzes and character profiles on Batman and his famous teammates and villains!

Each action-packed issue includes a new comic strip featuring a team-up between Batman and one of his Super Hero friends. From Green Lantern to The Flash, Blue Beetle to Wonder Woman, there’s something in it for any Super Hero fan!

volume.name: Batman: The Brave and the Bold

description:
Welcome to The Dark Knight, where the cracked and criminal side of Gotham City reigns! After the epic chaos of our last seven issues, we’re showcasing two self-contained cases… that may have huge repercussions in the months to come! PLUS! Don’t forget to have your say in the letters column!

Inside the latest issue:

BATMAN: THE DARK KNIGHT - THE MADNESS

People are apparently killing themselves in the abandoned subway tunnels underneath Gotham City – and Batman is determined to trackdown the madman responsible.

BATMAN: DETECTIVE COMICS - SCARE TACTICS

Catwoman has been hired to steal something – but Batman is more interested in the fact that she’s been poisoned by the Scarecrow! The night only gets crazier from there!

In a galaxy where evil is an ever-present danger, you can always count on the likes of R2-D2 and C-3PO to deliver one-liners and keep spirits high in times of crisis! Don't miss some astromech amusement in the next chapters of Dark Times: Out of the Wilderness and The Old Republic: The Lost Suns, featuring in Star Wars Galaxy #15!

Plus, Qui-Gon's adventure on Telos IV nears its climax in Jedi: The Dark Side!

Star Wars Galaxy takes a break from Dark Times in issue #16 - we bring you a Vader story we just couldn't keep back any longer in the shape of Star Wars: Purge!

Qui-Gon's faces the ultimate test in the thrilling climax of Jedi: The Dark Side, while Theron Shan's adventures in The Old Republic continue!

Unless you’ve been living under a rock these past few months, we’re sure it hasn't escaped your attention that Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace is being released in cinemas in mind-blowing 3D this February!

Star Wars Galaxy marks the occasion with an all-action story featuring the big, bad Sith, Darth Maul, as he takes on Lord Vader in a high-octane battle for survival! Resurrection is a Star Wars tale that you won't want to miss - and you can check out preview artwork below! Also included in this issue is a fantastic Darth Maul poster - again, check it out on this page.

Elsewhere in the issue there's the grand finale of Republic spy Theron Shan's adventure in The Lost Suns! Will it be a happily ever after for Shan and his unlikely comrades? After taking a break in the last issue, we return to the Dark Times as Darth Vader and an unknown assassin continue to stalk their prey: Jedi Dass Jennir.

Another issue of Star Wars Galaxy, another awesome finale! To celebrate the release of Star Wars: Episode 1 - The Phantom Menace in 3D, we've got the fantastic second half of our Maul vs Vader two-parter, Resurrection! It's so good, it's literally jumping off the page!

Plus, we're kicking off the next arc of the Invasion series, Revelations, with two stunning chapters featuring one of the most popular characters in Star Wars lore, Luke Skywalker! After the startling climax to Invasion: Rescues a few issues ago, a new chapter begins for the Galfridian family, as siblings Kaye and Finn come face to face with their new destinies. Will they be able to navigate the difficult path ahead?

We know there's nothing like the dulcet tones of a Wookiee's roar to put a smile on your face - Chewbacca and Han Solo make guest appearances in the latest issue of Star Wars Galaxy! In the first part of Agent Of The Empire: Iron Eclipse, secret agent Jahan Cross gets a close encounter of the furred kind when he runs into Chewie and Solo while investigating stolen droid technology. You'd be mad to miss this thrilling adventure from inside the Empire!

Plus, after a short hiatus, Dark Times: Out Of The Wilderness is back with the penultimate chapter. Falco Sang has got Jedi Dass Jennir in his sights, but he gets more than he bargained for when he encounters Jennir's feisty female friend, Ember Chankeli! Finally, the next chapter of Invasion: Revelations sets a new course for our heroes as the Yuuzhan Vong launch another deadly attack. Yikes!

Dawn of the Jedi: Force Storm - Part 1 of 5

Witness the origins of the Jedi in this all-new story! An order or warrior monks strive to maintain peace and balance the power known only as 'the Force'. But there is evil on the horizon as a stranger threatens to destroy the harmony of the galaxy and plunge it into darkness.

Agent of the Empire: Iron Eclipse - Part 3 of 5

On the hunt for the stolen droid technology, Imperial agent Jahan Corss has become a wanted man! With his droid destroyed, Cross is alone and on the run, but there might just be two smugglers with a very fast ship who can help him out...

Invasion: Revelations - Part 5 of 5

Revelations lives up to its name! Secrets are uncovered and true intentions come to light! What does the future hold for Finn Galfridian and his family? Find out in this final chapter.

Blood Ties: Boba Fett is Dead - Part 1 of 4

The greatest bounty hunter in the galaxy, dead!? Blasted from here to eternity, Boba Fett lies alone in the desert. But that is just the beginning of the story! As news of his death reaches far and wide across the galaxy, someone rises to avenge him! Who is this mysterious being and what is their connection to Boba Fett?

Dawn of the Jedi: Force Storm - Part 2 of 5

The origin of the Jedi continues! A great darkness is sweeping the galaxy, but only a select few are aware of its presence. More mysteries behind the Jedi Order are revealed!

Agent of the Empire: Iron Eclipse - Part 4 of 5

Action! Adventure! Intrigue! And the Millennium Falcon! What more could you want from a Star Wars story? In this penultimate chapter, find out the true purpose behind 'Iron Eclipse'. If you like droids, then you'll love this!

DAWN OF THE JEDI: FORCE STORM - Part 3 of 5

The Force Hound Xesh has revealed himself to the three young Je’daii – now they battle for the Force and their lives! But live or die, the storm that will engulf their homeworld has already begun!

AGENT OF THE EMPIRE: IRON ECLIPSE - Part 5 of 5

Agent Jahan Cross vs. a deadly, psychopathic spider cyborg! What could go wrong? More Han! More Chewie! Don’t miss the pulse-pounding finale to Agent of the Empire!

BLOOD TIES: BOBA FETT IS DEAD! - Part 2 of 4

Shot down and left for dead in the desert, the once great bounty hunter, Boba Fett, is no more. But is it really that easy? A mysterious avenger continues their search for Boba Fett’s killers, drawing Fett’s clone relation, Connor Freeman, into the fold! Plus, a shocking revelation!

Blood Ties: Boba Fett is Dead - Final Chapter

Connor Freeman, the half-clone, half-brother of Boba Fett, has been tasked with protecting the former wife and daughter of the galaxy's greatest bounty hunter! Meanwhile, back from the dead, Fett is on a mission to discover why he was made a target, and has crashlanded on the planet Blackfel - only to come face to face with Darth Vader.

Dawn of the Jedi: Force Storm - Final Chapter

The fate of the galaxy rests in the hands of three young Je'daii Journeyers, who were all 'called' to a crash site on the planet of Tython! Working together to repel the powerful Force sensitive, Xesh, the Je'daii are now in pursuit! At the Abyss of Ruh, the Force storm has arrived, threatening to unleash the beasts who dwell within!
